<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-12-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-12-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="312" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d312">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">701.9411/1537a: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Grew</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-12-07">December 7, 1941</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>820. Following action has been taken today. Immediately upon
                                receiving news of the Japanese attack upon Hawaii, the American
                                Government took steps to see that absolute protection was accorded
                                the Japanese official establishments and official personnel within
                                the jurisdiction of the United States.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>